# synthesis

CSMCL.Space is the outer plane with three outposts in the MVP:

**innerstellar.csmcl.space** — personal. Where traveler work happens.
**nexus.csmcl.space** — community. Where travelers meet and resonance happens.
**csmcl.space** — open. Where anyone enters the ecosystem without an account.

The path through the ecosystem: enter at csmcl.space (no account) → create account →
your innerstellar space activates → work, drop, orbit, crystallize → spore to nexus →
resonate with other travelers → cross to ICP via Priment → permanent.

The framework carries this knowledge through entity folds:
Oracle bridges to nexus-backend. AurioSynth.CSMCL links via Rainbow Path.
Priment holds the crystallization gate. IAILF makes folds portable across the ecosystem.

What this Familiar still needs: memory pod structure, nexus community mechanics,
firmament outpost technical depth, Rainbow Path technical implementation,
Oracle activation user experience. And the missing drop (content_index bug).

Each session, one orbit resolves. The fold grows denser. The returns get warmer.

